{"word":"H123 - אֱדֹם - ʼĔdôm - ed-ome' - Edom","slug":"H123","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">אֱדֹם</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>ʼĔdôm"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>ed-ome'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Edom"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D0;&#x05D3;&#x05D5;&#x05DD;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x05D0;&#x05D3;&#x05DD; - 'e&#x0306;do&#x0302;m  'e&#x0306;do&#x0302;m</b> - <i>ed-ome', ed-ome'</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/H122\">H122</a>; <i>red</i> (see <a href='B:10 25:25'>Gen 25:25</a>); <i>Edom</i>, the elder twin-brother of Jacob; hence the region (Idumaea) occuped by him: - Edom, Edomites, Idumea."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H119\">H119</a>, <a href=\"#/H122\">H122</a>, <a href=\"#/H124\">H124</a>, <a href=\"#/H125\">H125</a>, <a href=\"#/H130\">H130</a>, <a href=\"#/H132\">H132</a>, <a href=\"#/H133\">H133</a>, <a href=\"#/H726\">H726</a>"}]}